<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-365-826  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 365 826.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  June 22 1989 n1204* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Interactive Systems answers Santa Cruz Operation by unbundling itsUnix.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Interactive Systems Corp. (marketing)Santa Cruz Operation Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyUnbundlingUNIXContractsSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>INTERACTIVE SYSTEMS ANSWERS SANTA CRUZ OPERATION BYandM;UNBUNDLING ITS UNIXandM;Eastman Kodak-owned Unix operating system supplier InteractiveandM;Systems Corp, Santa Monica, California is fighting back with its own newmarketing strategy following the launch of Open Desktop by its rival SantaCruz Operation at UniForum earlier this year.andP;  But instead of opting for alow-cost bundling deal like Open Desktop, Interactive has un-bundled itsproducts into a series of Unix system software modules, allowing systemsdesigners and resellers to choose their own configuration.andP;  Interactive'sArchitech Series packages the modules into three main areas - application,network and workstation - allowing configurations ranging from non-networkedrun-time environments to full software development platforms.andP;  Along with thebase 386/ix System V.3.2compatible perating system, Interactive offersstarter, extender and developer configurations within the three categories.andO;An application starter system, for instance, is priced at $745 for a singleuser system including 386/ix operating system, VP/ix MS-DOS under Unix, theTen Plus user interface and documentation: a multi-user version costs $1,445.andO;An extender pack would also include PC-Interface, while the developer pack -priced at $1,445 single-user, $2,145 multi-user - has the full Unix softwaredevelopment system and text processing utilities.andP;  Network and workstationconfigurations can be configured in a similar way, including such componentsas TCP/IP, Network File System and X Window.andP;  Interactive has recently signedOEM deals with Bull SA and tiny UK computer manufacturer Jarogate Ltd ofSurbiton in Surrey, and has a major distribution agreement with Intra-UnixGmbH of Berlin.andO;</TEXT></DOC>